Living Status Effects
=====================

Burning, Bleeding, Chilled, Freezing, and Exposed are stored directly on
every living. Include <status_effects.h> and use the STATUS_* bit flags.
The flags are saved compatibility contracts; never renumber or reuse one.

Application
-----------
  varargs status apply_status_effect(int effect, int strength, int duration,
    object source, status silent)

Only one STATUS_* bit may be applied per call. duration is in seconds and is
rounded up to a two-second heartbeat. Burning derives its duration from its
stack count and ignores duration. source is optional and is converted to a
primitive identifier immediately; no object reference is saved.
Set silent for a refresh or transformation that should update state and GMCP
without producing application messages.

Prefer the named wrappers in normal content:

  target->apply_burning(stacks, attacker);
  target->apply_bleeding(strength, seconds, attacker);
  target->apply_chilled(seconds, attacker);
  target->apply_freezing(seconds, attacker);
  target->apply_exposed(seconds, attacker);

All functions return 1 when the effect was accepted and 0 for invalid input.

Queries And Removal
-------------------
  int query_status_effect_mask()
  status query_status_effect(int mask)
  int query_status_effect_strength(int effect)
  int query_status_effect_remaining(int effect)
  int query_status_effect_duration(int effect)
  object query_status_effect_source(int effect)
  mapping query_status_effects()
  varargs status remove_status_effect(int mask, status silent)
  void clear_all_status_effects()

Queries and removal may use combined masks. Strength and duration queries
require one exact bit. Source queries resolve the stored primitive identifier
to a currently loaded living, or return 0. For example, a cure for either
cold tier can use:

  target->remove_status_effect(STATUS_COLD);

query_status_effects() returns a deep copy. Do not inspect or modify the
living's saved state mapping directly.

Effect Contracts
----------------
  Burning X
    Adds stacks up to max(1, target level). Each heartbeat deals X fire
    damage, then replaces X with floor(X/2). The 1-stack tick is final.

  Bleeding X
    Adds strength up to max(5, target level/5). X is added to melee damage
    before defensive modifiers and absorption. Movement has a 25 percent
    chance to deal X slash damage. The caller supplies the duration.

  Chilled / Freezing
    Chilled reduces final swings by 10 percent and adds 1 second to new
    set_spell_limit() cooldowns. Applying Chilled twice promotes it to
    Freezing. Freezing uses 20 percent and 2 seconds. Direct Freezing is
    allowed. These do not affect custom call_out or soul-owned timers.

  Exposed
    Adds 5 percentage points to incoming critical chance. It does not stack;
    reapplication keeps the longer duration.

Lifecycle And Display
---------------------
State is primitive and saved on the living. Timers pause when the player
object is absent and resume after restore. Death clears all effects. The
`buffs` command and Char.Defences GMCP list expose them as non-clearable
debuffs. Add future display names to GLOBAL_STATUS_EFFECT_MAPPING in
<buffs.h>; do not put these bit flags in GLOBAL_DEBUFF_MAPPING.
